stem: "Student writes \`int MAX = 700;\` (no const). Compiler reaction?"
source: 
  kind: "v2"
  ref: "v2:Q4 — trace: forgot const → VLA (off-scope behaviour)"
commonMistakeIds: []
status: "NEW"
authoringStatus: "DRAFT"
createdBy: "SA-L4-Q4"
correct: "Error: array bound is not a compile-time constant."
distractors: 
  - "Warning only — compiles and runs."
  - "Same as const — compiles cleanly."
  - "Linker error at fn call site."
explanation: "C++ fixed-size array bound MUST be compile-time constant. A non-const int does not qualify, so MAX[arr] fails at compile time."
